result.execSummary:
The defendant Ann M. Dittmann was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Issue of Worthless Checks(<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.24(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 11:10 AM: Defendant Ann M. Dittmann in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant and Atty Szilagyi appear via video from the WC Jail.

Case called @ 1:01 p.m.  Defendant Ann M. Dittmann in court, in custody, appears via video with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  ADA Anderson - DE will be entering a plea and matter to be set for sentencing at a later date to allow time for DE to pay the restitution in full. Statement by Atty Szilagyi reciting the agreement reached.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant will be represented by SPD. DE waives her right to be personally present in the courtroom. Plea colloquy entertained. Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: Guilty. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court orders $500 Sig Bond.   SEH Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for February 23, 2016 at 11:00 am.

Case Called @ 2:08 PM: Defendant Ann M. Dittmann not in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court received information from the Clerk that Def had called with information she had a doctor's appointment today and could not be here.  Arrest Warrant authorized with Statewide Extradition.    Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.
